songs.title: Out of My Limit (Live)
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Ashton]
1 2 3 4

[Verse 1: Luke & Calum]
Back in high school we used to take it slow
Red lipstick on and high heel stilettos
Had a job downtown working the servo
Had me waiting in line, couldn’t even let go, c'mon

[Pre-Chorus: Calum]
Cause I never wanna be that guy
Who doesn’t even get a taste
No more having to chase
To win that prize

[Chorus: All]
You’re just a little bit out of my limit
It’s been two years now, haven’t even seen the best of me
And in my mind now I’ve been over this a thousand times
But it’s almost over, let’s start over

[Verse 2: Calum]
Back in high school we used to make up plans
Called you up one day to meet split ends

[Pre-Chorus: Calum]
Cause I never wanna be that guy
Who doesn’t even get a taste
No more having to chase
To win that prize

[Chorus: All]
You’re just a little bit out of my limit
It’s been two years now you haven’t even seen the best of me
And in my mind now I’ve been over this a thousand times
Cause it’s almost over, let’s start over

[Bridge: Michael]
Guitar solo

[Chorus: All & Luke]
You’re just a little bit out of my limit
Lemme see your hands
It’s been two years now, haven’t even seen the best of me
And in my mind now I’ve been over this a thousand times
Cause it’s almost over, let’s start over

[Outro: Luke]
Alright
